Industry competition
Distribution Transformer
     High quality distribution transformer has many supporting factors for 
production such as choosing the quality of the materials and modern 
machineries. The demand for distribution transformer depends on the demand 
of the electrical energy accounted for the local gross domestic production 
(GDP) in 2003, 2004, 2005 equivalent to 18,121.40, 19,325.80 and 21,143 
megawatts respectively or the growth rate accounted for 8.63, 6.65, and 9.40 
per cent respectively. This coincides with the stable GDP growth rate 
(at 1988 prices). In 2003, 2004, and 2005 the growth rate accounted for 
7.00, 6.20, and 4.50 per cent respectively. Currently, AKR is the leading 
company for distribution transformer with an average market share of 21.63 
per cent in 2001-2004, and having competitors such as Thai Maxwell Co.,Ltd, 
Tirathai Plc., Precise Electric Manufacturing Co.,Ltd., and Charoenchai 
Transformer Co.,Ltd.

Service
     The service that AKR provides include maintenance, modification and 
repair of transformers. The company has 10 sales and service centers 
nationwide, an important support for sales and services to customers. 
The company provides maintenance and repair for every brands. 
     Service industry has a tendency to grow depending on the demand and 
sales of transformers such as maintenance service in large industries. 
Competition is not fierce. The company has strong points to provide service 
as it has 10 sales and service centers nationwide. The main competitors 
are Thai Maxwell Co.,Ltd., R-Support co.,Ltd., ABB Co.,Ltd., Charoenchai 
Transformer Co.,Ltd. and Tirathai Plc.

Energy  
     The relentless rises in oil prices continue to pose a threat to the
environment including the government policy to support the production of 
electricity from solar cells. The Project to expand service from solar 
cells (Demand of electricity totally projects 36 megawatts).The policy 
to generate high quality electricity for the public coincides with the 
development of alternative energy according to the Strategy of National 
Energy. The target is to increase the alternative energy from 0.5 per cent
in 2002 to 8 per cent of the commercial energy in 2011 as there is a 
tendency to produce energy from solar cell in Thailand. 
     Alternative energy is competitive since the electrical installation 
service industry is growing, paving ways for new companies, engaged in solar 
energy to be established and more competitive. With the current competitors 
and intense competition, the company still has advantages over other companies, 
as the solar module made from Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. can control the cost and 
pricing and competition for energy conservation is not intense. 

Solar Cells     
     The tendency for solar cell industrial growth is high as the country's 
strategy is more stable and there is an increasing potential for competition. 
Nevertheless, Thailand does not have sufficient energy reserves for the 
increasing demand. In 2002, The Strategy of National Energy aimed to increase
the ratio of energy substitution from 0.5 per cent to 8 per cent of the 
commercial energy in 2011. Local competition is still intense since local 
solar cell manufacturers such as Solartron Plc., Bangkok Solar Co.,Ltd., 
have a capacity to produce 74 megawatts of energy per year. The percentage 
is higher than demand for solar cell as there is still some uncertainty. 
However, Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd., can still produce solar cell for overseas 
which during 1997-2004 the average solar cell world market expansion accounts 
for 38.38 per cent. 

Type of customers
(1) Distribution Transformer
     Oil Type Distribution Transformer aims state-owned enterprise customers
and other industrial customers. Important state-owned enterprises are EGAT, 
PEA. The industries are expanding their distribution transformer. 
The main customers are mainly the public sector comprising of PEA and EGAT, 
whereas the private sector comprises of large, well-known companies. 
In 2005, the users were mostly private sectors, public sectors and overseas 
accounting for Baht 766.02, 394.73 and 96.22 million, calculated as 60.94, 
31.40 and 7.66 per cent respectively. 

(2) Service
     The target groups for service are private sectors that already used 
distribution transformers. Currently, there are more than 100,000 transformers 
used in various industries, of which 30,000 transformers come from AKR. 
AKR is advantageous as it has sales and service centers all over the country 
to provide maintenance service for other brands. The company cans an issue 
safety certificate to assure their maintenance, modification & repair services 
to large industries. 

(3) Energy
     The main solar energy users from public sectors such as PEA, Department
of alternative Energy, etc., including schools, public health centers in rural 
areas. AKR's achievements are their solar module and solar homes the southern 
provinces. There is a tendency to increase use because of the government 
policy. 
     Other target groups are the private sectors such as hotels, resorts, 
private residences that are not under the supervision of PEA service or 
non-transformer users. Upgrading the energy is required to preserve clean
energy for the community's environment. 

Environmental impacts
     Since established in 1981, AKR and its subsidiaries have no litigation 
cases concerning the environmental impact. AKR obtained ISO 14001 for 
environmental systems and standards. AKR also obtained ISO 9001: 2000 for
production quality control, hygiene management and safety and OHAS 18001 
for occupational health and safety zone.

Summary of material contracts
1)  Machinery purchasing agreement 
     Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. entered into a solar cell machinery purchasing 
agreement with Centrotherm Photovoltaics GmbH+Co.KG ("Centrotherm") Germany. 
Centrotherm is an expertise in producing turnkey solar cell that are
produced from the 20 minor steps of the production line from 10 different 
machines and is well-known for its efficiency, yield and production efficiency. 
     (1) Value Agreement and Payment Conditions
     Value of Machines   Approximately Euro 17.7 million 
                         (excluding transportation fee) 
                         (Baht 900 million including transportation fee) 
                         (Exchange rate 1 Euro = 50 Baht)
     Delivery period     21 months after the final QC (August 2005- March 2007)
     (2) Responsibilities of Centrotherm
     * Find good quality machines to produce solar cell that produces silicone 
       that has a production capacity of 25 megawatts per annum with 1 year 
       spare parts warranty.
     * Manage and plan the project until completion of the project.
     * Provide theoretical and practical trainings for employees at Ekarat 
       Solar Co.,Ltd. regarding the transporting the machines into the factory 
       until the final process, how to operate the machine, the production 
       modification process and maintenance.
     * Site Acceptance Test.
     (3) Warranty
     Machine Warranty
        * Centrotherm provides 1 year warranty for the machine and its spare
          parts (except depreciation from its conditions, equipments produced
          from quartz and graphite, lamp, etc) 
        * Centrotherm provides warranty of the value no higher than 17.7 
          million Euro (approx. Baht 885 million) for any damage that may 
          occur to the property or personnel's of Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. 
     Warranty for the efficiency of Solar Cell
        * The average efficiency of modifying the multi-crystal silicon 
          energy of solar cell is 14.5 per cent and the lowest efficiency 
          is 12 per cent while the average modification efficiency for 
          single solar cell is 15.5 per cent and the lowest efficiency 
          is 13 per cent.
        * The highest production rate is 24.7 megawatts (for solar cell 
          size 156 mm x 156 mm).
        * Yield is not lesser than 92 per cent or wastage not over 8 
          per cent.

