Feasibility Study       
     Solar Cell Project
     The possibility to produce solar cell of Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. with 
the possibility from research are as follows: 
     Ekarat Engineering Public Co.,Ltd.
      - Study on the technology to produce solar cell
      - Status and tendency of solar cell industry
      - Evaluation on the solar cell investment interest
      - Solar cell technology suitability for investment
      - Possibility to produce solar cell 
      - Project Characteristics
      - Investment Risk
     ACAP Advisory Public Company Limited
      - Project Return Analysis

     From the study of the possibility, the project will estimate the 
project at the beginning of 2007 where the estimation is 50 per cent 
of production capacity or equal to 12.62 million watts. In 2008, the 
increased production capacity is 80 per cent or equal to 20.19 million 
watts. Full capacity production will start in 2009 to an equivalent 
of 25.24 million watts. 
     Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. will pay for the pre-operating expense 
during 2006 for the test run of Baht 144.39 million , amortized as 
expense for 5 years. Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. has a privilege from BOI 
to produce alternative energy within 8 years without income tax.
     In 2007, the operation results is Baht 1,514 million and cost 
of sales is Baht 1,335 million. Profit before interest expenses is 
Baht 65.65 million. Since the company has to pay interest expenses 
of Baht 74.65 million, the net loss is Baht 8.99 million. EBITDA is 
equal to Baht 172.71 million. The company is expected to profit in 
2008 when production increases of approximately Baht 2,423 million, 
a net profit of Baht 152.07 million. 

     The possibility of the 25 megawatts per annum solar cell 
project can be concluded as follow:
     Type of investment: 
          Additional investment of Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. with registered 
     capital of Baht 30 million to Baht 500 million. At the beginning period 
     AKR hold the share of Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. at the rate of 100 per cent 
     of totaling Baht 500 million at Baht 1 per share.

     Investment value: 
          Totaling Investment is approximately Baht 1,409 million. Debt to 
     Equity Ratio not exceeding 2:1 (excluding current liabilities)

     Source of investment: 
          At the beginning period payment for the machinery are loan from a 
     commercial bank. 

     Return on Investment: 
          IRR equals to 31.54 per cent. NPV, calculating the discounted rate 
     at 20 per cent and the terminal Value is 3 times the EBITDA is equal to 
     Baht 423 million (The feasibility use Discounted rate at 20 per cent which
     return on investment rate that AKR and its subsidiary accepted.)

     Investment period:      Production in the first quarter of 2007.
     Payback period:         5 years
     Expected benefit:       Reduce cost of solar module production

Technical and Management Assistant 
     AKR received technology transfer from many companies such as technology
transfer on design and producing sealed oil & dry cast resin distribution 
transformer from Starkstrom-Geratebau GmbH, Germany 

Future Projects Solar 
     Cell factory have a 25 megawatts production capacity per annum using wafer 
as a raw material to produce electrical energy from solar energy. Acids and 
chemicals and place in an oven at a high temperature absorbing the mixed 
chemicals clean the wafer. Phosphorous causes the wafer to produce electricity
arty phosphorous. The wafer is coated to protect the reflection of the sun. 
An electrical magnet is produced and the solar cell will produce a hot heat 
to produce energy. The solar cell is used as raw materials at Ekarat Solar 
Co.,Ltd. At present Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. is selling silicon solar Module by 
importing the solar cells and assemble the solar cell locally. This project 
is expanded to serve the related business of the company with details 
as follow: 
     Project Location:      AMATA City Industrial Estate, Rayong province 
     Project Duration:      August 2005 - March 2007
     Area                   15 rais
     Building               Factory size 50 X 60 meters with 5,000 square meter
     Production Capacity    Approximately 25 megawatts per annum
     Wafer size             15.6 cm. X 15.6 cm
     Highest output         3.53 watts/cell
     Amount of cells produced   7.15 million cells per annum
     No of employees        Approximately 94 persons (3 shifts)

Types of Solar Cells
     Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd decides to invest in 2 types of crystalline 
solar cells:
     1. Mono or Single Crystalline Silicon Solar Cell which production 
and distribution in 2003 accounts for 200.47 megawatts, a 26.94 per cent 
of the world's market share.
     2. Multi Crystalline Silicon Solar Cell which production and 
distribution in 2003 accounts for 459.80 megawatts, a 61.79  per cent of 
the worlds markets share.
     Therefore, Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. can produce single silicon and 
multi-crystalline solar cell by changing the wafer only. 

Investment
     This project requires Baht 1,400 million for investment and Debt to 
Equity Ratio not exceeding 2:1 (excluding current liabilities). Sources 
of investment and sources of investment expense 
are as follows:
     Source of investment 
        Investment              500     million baht 
        Long-term loans         900     million baht total   Baht 1,400 million
     Source of Investment Expense
        Land                     26     million baht 
        Construction, Factory   260     million baht
        Machines & tools        900     million baht
        Equipment, furniture     19     million baht 
        Vehicles                 10     million baht 
        Other assets             50     million baht 
        Test Run                144     million baht  total   Baht 1,409 million 
     Working Capital from loans Baht 450 million 

