Historical background
         Ekarat Engineering Public Co.,Ltd.("AKR" or "the company") was 
established on June 24, 1981 with registered capital investment of Baht 4
 million to rise gradually by group Noichaiboon,big groups of shareholders.
 The company was registered as a public company in 1994. In 1997, the copany
 was affected by the economic crisis with a loss so the company had to restructure
 the company in 2003 and restructure its financial status to be financially free by
 having new shareholders by having V&A Holdings Co.,Ltd. (Raksriaksorn
 Group) and Kamnerdngam to be their big shareholders. The court declared 
the company bankrupt without any restructuring in 2004 on the condition that the
 new shareholders - Raksriaksorn Group and Kamnerdngam invest in the business
 and the process must be completed by December 31, 2004. However the management 
had sold off the investment capital and discontinued business with the 8 affiliates
 (Ekarat Generator Co.,Ltd., Ekarat Marketing Co.,Ltd., Theparak Transformer 
Co.,Ltd., E.R. Metal Works Co.,Ltd., Ekarat International Co.,Ltd., Nepal Ekar
at Engineering Co.,Pvt.Ltd., Myanmar Ekarat Transformer Co.,Ltd. and Ekarat  
Transformer(M) SDN.Bhd.) On December 30, 2004, E.K.R. Holdings Co.,Ltd
. including transferred claimant right on debt with the 5 subsidiaries and associated 
companies to E.K.R. Holdings Co.,Ltd. In 2005, the company increased its
 registered share capital from the former amount of Baht 508.17 million to new 
registered share capital of Baht 608.17 million by proposing the shares at Baht 
2 per share. Currently AKR has 1 subsidiary - Ekarat Solar Co.,Ltd. which is
 engaged in manufacturing solar cell.  
