Dividend Policy         
         The Company and its subsidiary company have a policy to pay a cash
 dividend approximately 50 per cent of net profit after tax and legal reserve 
each year. The AKR's Board of Directors have the authority to operate 
according to the company's policy from time to time by processing under
 the conditions of the shareholders such as reserves for liabilities and 
business expansion or other factors related to the company's operation
al and managerial. This must be approved by the shareholders' meeting
 in parallel with AKR's Board of Directors.

According to loan agreement with a commercial specific that if the company
 intends to pay dividend for year 2004 performance onwards, the company
 must not delay the payment, or any liabilities or interest or fee as of the stated
date. If payment is not made to the bank, a written consent must be sent to the
bank within 15 days.  

