The scope of power, authority and responsibility 
        1. To review the sufficiency and creditability of the financial reports of
 the Company.
        2. To ensure, in co-ordination with the auditor and internal auditor, that the
 Company has efficient internal control and internal and it systems. 
        3. To review that the Company has risk management in material areas with 
sufficiency.
        4. To review compliance with the Securities and Exchange Act, regulations
of the SET and any other relevant regulations or laws.
        5. To present the Audit Committee Report to the Board at least once each
 quarter. The report contains the auditor and internal control team suggestions
 and the monitoring of the Company's management to the said suggestions. 
        6. To consider, appoint, and propose the auditors and the audit fee.
        7. To ensure the Company conforms to all regulations concerning connected
 transaction, disclosures or conflict of interest disclosures according to the SET.
        8. To take care of any other matter assigned to it by the Board of Directors
 and Audit Committee has been approved. 
        9. To prepare the monitoring report of the Audit Committee, which shall 
be disclosed in the Company's annual report and signed by the Chairman of the
Audit Committee.
        Responsibility of the Audit Committed
        The Audit Committee has duty and responsibility to the Board of Directors
 according to assign from its Board of Directors. Meanwhile, any responsibilities 
of the Board of Directors for the assigned job related to the external party who
still is the committee.

